Li Chien, 30, had been visiting a pub in Xiulin Township, north-eastern Taiwan .
He became annoyed with a dog owned by neighbour Tang Chao, 40, on his way home .
When police arrived they found the dog dead in a pool of blood .
The animal was found hours later by his distraught owner Tang Chao .
If the dog had been a stray, he would have faced no charges .